reviews.headline: Neutrogena Hydro Boost Gel Cleanser
reviews.comments: This is an amazing facial cleanser! It's super gentle on your skin, very hydrating, and removes makeup! I would definitely recommend!

I have been using this product for a while now and I absolutely love it. I like how it cleans my pores and deeply gets in there. I'm combination to oily skin and I feel like this best suits my skin and has helped with my acne problems scan as well.

reviews.headline: As a dry skin girl, I love it so far!
reviews.comments: I'm 27, have naturally dry/fairly untextured skin, and I don't have acne but my skin does have breakouts that can last days/weeks to over a month. I currently have a breakout and decided to try this since I ran out of cleanser and most Neutrogena products work amazingly for my skin. It's been a week and I love it - my skin feels clean and soft after using it, without it completely stripping my face. It also hasn't worsened my current breakout in anyway. Exactly what I wanted. If your skin type sounds like mine I'd recommend this.

reviews.headline: Why use anything else?
reviews.comments: It's gentle, removes makeup and mascara, even cleans the washcloth pretty well after cleaning your face. I thought this one was a keeper, but now, I'm noticing they are raising the price every time I buy it. May start shopping for a different product soon, but for now, this is my favorite.

reviews.headline: AVOID- dry and sensitive skin
reviews.comments: I have sensitive combo-dry skin. I've been trying to eliminate as much fragrance (artifical fragrance specifically), and I like the fragrance free version moisturizer in this line, so I thought I'd give this a try. It felt nice and smooth, but immediately after I rinsed my face, it felt SUPER dry and tight. I ended up putting on the very hydrating moisturizer I use at night and it hardly helped. Would not recommend.

reviews.comments: I have very sensitive skin that is very acne prone and this cleanser helped me so much. I always recommend it to my friends and family. It cleared my skin up almost 100% in about 3 weeks. I noticed a big difference within just a week. Amazing product!

faceoff_positive.comments: I struggle with really dry skin during the winter months. My face will feel really tight and I'll even get small dry patches by my ears and on my chin, so needless to say I was very excited when Home Testers Club sent me Neutrogena's Hydro Boost Hydrating Cleansing Gel in exchange for my honest thoughts. This gentle, lightweight foaming facial cleanser is dermatologist recommended, hypoallergenic, fragrance free, non-comedogenic, oil free, soap free, Paraben free, dye free, Phthalate free and alcohol free. The hydro boost replenishes water and helps to improve your skin's moisture barrier which results in smooth, hydrated skin. This cleanser transforms into a silky lather that removes dirt, oil, makeup and all those other icky impurities. It's clinically proven to increase skin's hydration level and lock it in. I use this cleanser every morning and night and I don't have to worry about my skin feeling like every drop of moisture has been sucked out! Lol. My face feels hydrated and soft
faceoff_positive.headline: It's like a big drink of water for your skin!

faceoff_negative.comments: I have dry, sensitive, acne prone skin which this is marketed for but after using this, my skin was very dry and irritated. I also found it hard to rinse from my skin feeling kind of slimy. I am not sure if it left something behind that my skin then reacted to but I would be cautious if you decide to try this with my skin type.
